                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d651">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.635 Neep/54: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-05T00:00:00-00:44"
                            >March 5, 1938—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received March 6—8:50
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Referring to your 9, March 3, 5 p.m., I am informed by President Barclay that
                    he conferred with Caffe yesterday and that he has <pb facs="0789" n="781"
                        xml:id="pg_781"/> cabled his Minister at Paris as outlined in penultimate
                    paragraph of my 14, February 21, 4 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
